| Web Static Content System | `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/features/staticPages`, `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/features/staticPages/content` | Shared branded content shell plus route-driven content modules for public info/legal pages | Powers `HowWeWork`, `AboutUs`, `CoreValues`, `ComingSoon`, `FrequentlyAskedQuestions`, `PolicyPages`, `GenericPages`, `PrivacyPolicy`, and `TermsServices`; remaining manual-wrapper marketing pages are now outside this system |
| Web Auth Surface | `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/features/auth`, `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/pages/Login`, `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/pages/Signup`, `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/pages/Otp` | OTP-driven traveler signup/login/verification flow | All auth routes now funnel through `AuthLayout` |
| Web Protected Flow Features | `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/features/booking`, `paymentMethods`, `travelersInfo`, `remainingPayment`, `bookingStatus` | Shared hooks/components for protected booking and account flows | Core state ownership is centralized, but several route owners still branch desktop/mobile layouts inside the route file |
| Web API Layer | `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/api` | Website auth/listing/booking API clients | Highest endpoint density in `apiService.js` |
| Web Context and Guard Layer | `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/context`, `Huz-Web-Frontend/src/components/ProtectedRoute` | App-level auth, currency, booking state, and guarded navigation | `App.js` wraps all routes in `AuthContextProvider`, `CurrencyProvider`, and `BookingProvider` |
